  the  paper  is  had  know ,  the Q  The answer must be a situation when a person with mental illness is able to do what a normal person can do, but with some help or some things that the person can't do without the help of others. A person with mental illness can lead a relatively normal life with some help, and the help is managed. The person is effectively treated, which is a good situation for the person to lead a normal life. The person is not able to lead a normal life all the time, so the person is managed. The person's mental illness can recur, and the person can be effectively treated, but the person is not able to lead a normal life all the time. The person's mental illness can cause delusion, but the person is able to lead a relatively normal life with some help. So the answer is managed (a).

